From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0036/N] vm_version_bsd_aarch64: CheriBSD stub for get_os_cpu_info

`VM_Version::get_os_cpu_info` is entirely Apple-specific:

  - `hw.optional.floatingpoint`, `hw.optional.neon`,
    `hw.optional.armv8_crc32`, `hw.optional.armv8_1_atomics` are
    macOS-only sysctls.
  - `HW_CACHELINE` (used with `CTL_HW`) is a macOS sysctl
    identifier.
  - `hw.cpufamily` is the macOS CPU-family probe.
  - The final `_cpu = CPU_APPLE;` assignment makes no sense on
    CheriBSD.

Wrap the Apple body in `#ifdef __APPLE__` and add a CheriBSD branch
that sets conservative defaults:

  - `_features = CPU_FP | CPU_ASIMD | CPU_CRC32 | CPU_LSE`
    (Morello is ARMv8.6+, so all four are mandated).
  - 64-byte i-cache / d-cache lines (Morello R1/N1-class).
  - `_zva_length = 64`, then refined by reading `DCZID_EL0` (the
    inline-asm in the Apple branch is portable, kept verbatim).
  - `_model = 0; _cpu = CPU_ARM;` (generic ARM tag).

Phase 2 can replace the conservative defaults with real probing
via `ID_AA64ISAR0_EL1` / `ID_AA64PFR0_EL1` reads.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0036)

--- a/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/vm_version_bsd_aarch64.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/vm_version_bsd_aarch64.cpp
@@ -41,6 +41,7 @@
   return -1;
 }

+#ifdef __APPLE__
 static bool cpu_has(const char* optional) {
   uint32_t val;
   size_t len = sizeof(val);
@@ -49,8 +50,10 @@
   }
   return val;
 }
+#endif

 void VM_Version::get_os_cpu_info() {
+#ifdef __APPLE__
   size_t sysctllen;

   // hw.optional.floatingpoint always returns 1, see
@@ -90,6 +93,27 @@
   }
   _model = family;
   _cpu = CPU_APPLE;
+#else
+  // FreeBSD/CheriBSD: hw.optional.* and HW_CACHELINE are Apple-specific.
+  // Set conservative defaults; Phase 2 can probe ID_AA64ISAR0_EL1 etc.
+  // for real feature detection. Morello aarch64 always has FP + ASIMD;
+  // CRC32 + LSE are required by ARMv8.1 baseline (Morello is v8.6+).
+  _features = CPU_FP | CPU_ASIMD | CPU_CRC32 | CPU_LSE;
+  _icache_line_size = 64;
+  _dcache_line_size = 64;
+  _zva_length = 64;  // typical for ARMv8 cores
+
+  uint64_t dczid_el0;
+  __asm__ (
+    "mrs %0, DCZID_EL0\n"
+    : "=r"(dczid_el0)
+  );
+  if (!(dczid_el0 & 0x10)) {
+    _zva_length = 4 << (dczid_el0 & 0xf);
+  }
+  _model = 0;
+  _cpu = CPU_ARM;  // generic ARM; not CPU_APPLE
+#endif
 }

